svg:text.svg:tspan: In 1957, Russel Kirch scanned an photo of his son Walden,
converting the picture into a digital file. This was the first ever digital
image created. It was a significant milestone in the evolution of visual
technology, revolutionizing the way we capture, store and manipulate
pictures. The development of early digital cameras and scanners, which
enabled devices to convert light into digital data, started the trend that
has now become commonplace, and the transition from film to digital has
transformed numerous industries, from photography and medical imaging to
